1. Purpose

The Tamagotchi virtual pet app is mostly for entertainment purposes. It is a family-friendly game, which means anybody can play it. The Tamagotchi virtual pet is educational, mostly to kids, if you want them to be exposed to all kinds of topics that are associated with a Tamagotchi.

1. Design Considerations

The name of my mobile application is My Tamagotchi app.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

When the Start button is clicked then the user is prompted to start playing the game. It will move to the next screen where you can see 3 three buttons where you can click do certain activities with the pet, such as playing, feeding and bathing the dog.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

When you click the Feed button it will display an image of the pet eating. When you click the Play button it will display an image of the pet playing, and when you click the Wash it will display an image of the pet taking a bath.

**General Design**

The Tamagotchi virtual pet mobile application target audience is mostly children, but adults are also able play it too. The images and colors in the mobile application are attractive enough to grab the attention of a human being. Colors are used in the mobile application.

**Intuitive design**

The design of my Tamagotchi virtual pet mobile application is simple to navigate and understand. Users that will play this game will be able to go from one screen to another easily without experiencing any complications.

**Content prioritization**

The content displayed in this mobile application is essential to the users needs to use. It is attention grabbing for users with a very low concentration span. The background is not too complicated for the user, it is simple.

**Legible text content**

The text used in my Tamagotchi virtual pet mobile application is simply readable. The communication in this mobile application is clear and the instructions are clear to understand. The font size that I picked for this mobile application does not require the use of a magnifier, which means it is readable.

**Make interface elements clearly visible.**

The target audience of this Tamagotchi mobile app usually use their phones everywhere. This Tamagotchi virtual pet mobile app has sufficient background colour for people thatll play this game outdoors.

**Hand position control**

The hand positions in this Tamagotchi mobile application are placed in a suitable position, which accommodates the people that interact with their phones with their thumbs and the other 51% of people

**Images**

The pictures that I used easily grab the users attention as they are colorful and easy to understand**.** Children love to see colour, and the bet I chose for the mobile application has more than one colour which is black and white. This adds colour to the screen and it grabs the attention of the user.
